== Dice of Doom

Implementing the game from *Land of Lisp* in JS/Coffeescript/Node

=== install

Requires node => http://nodejs.org/
and the following libraries:
  coffee-script
  underscore
  socket.io

These are easily installed with npm => http://npmjs.org/
$ npm install coffee-script && npm install underscore && npm install socket.io

Also requires that `zepto.js` and `underscore.js` be in `public/`
for the HTML version.

=== play

the command line:
$ coffee src/cli.coffee

the HTML server:
$ coffee src/server.coffee
then, browse to 127.0.0.1:8124

=== next

Pretty graphics with Raphael.

=== history 

v0.0.1
Basic human vs. human play.

v0.0.2
Basic computer AI.

v0.0.3
Lazy evaluation of game trees. Basic heuristics for AI game
board rating.

v0.0.4
Vry basic node server and client interface that is still
essentially text. Use socket.io for persistence.
